<topic template="Default" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">PHAST Time Control Dialog Box</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">PHAST Time Control Dialog Box</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true"> PHAST Time Control</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is used to specify how the time step size varies period-by-period during the simulation. &#160;The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true"> PHAST Time Control</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is displayed by selecting </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Model|PHAST Time Control… </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> The user species a </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Time step length</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Ending time</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> when the time step length changes to another value or the simulation ends. &#160;The times entered in the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">PHAST Time Control</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box do not need to be the same as the times entered in other parts of the model. &#160;ModelMuse synthesizes all the times throughout the model and combines them to create the PHAST input file.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><anchor id="Start_time" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;"></anchor><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Start time</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> allows the calculations to begin at a time other than zero. &#160;This feature is useful for restart runs from the end of a previous calculation when chemical conditions were saved. See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Print_Frequency_Dialog_Box" anchor="Restart" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Restart</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Print_Frequency_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">PHAST Print Frequency</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
</topic>
